    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Oil Cooler and Filter Housing - Installation
        - Oil Filter Base and Housing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Oil Filter Base and Housing</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install intake manifold. See "Manifolds and Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR)".</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001030" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ13/J13039.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Latching return tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latching return tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latching return tube gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter housing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate a new latching return tube gasket with clean engine oil and install onto latching
                return tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install latching return tube by pushing down and twisting tube 120&#176; clockwise until
                latched.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001032" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ13/J13040.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter base and housing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Screw, (M6 x 25)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter base</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter housing gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil drain valve assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latching return tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter element</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter cap seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter cap</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new oil filter housing gasket between the housing and base.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install six M6 x 25 oil filter housing mounting screws and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_222.xml" xrefid="E30010B">special torque
                    <xref refid="E30010B"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3900008" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figN13/N13002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter housing assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter cap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 50 x 16 stud bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 25 screw (6)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter base</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 55 bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter housing assembly onto oil filter adapter and intake manifold.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install M8 x 55 bolt and two M8 x 50 x 16 stud bolts. Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque
                    <xref refid="S300GTG"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on the oil filter cap and lubricate with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter and cap as a combined unit. Tighten cap to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_222.xml" xrefid="E30010B">special torque
                    <xref refid="E30010B"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, add the correct viscosity oil to the engine before starting. See Engine
                    Operation and Maintenance Manual.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
